Kolomna 2010 1/2-1/2 (48)}) 11. Be3 {Black has a cramped position} Bd7 12. Rc1
{White has a very active position} Rc8 13. b3 {Controls a4} b6 14. Re1 Rb8 15.
Qc2 Qc8 16. Kh2 Ne8 {White has an active position} 17. Red1 f5 (17... Be5+ $5 {
should be considered} 18. Kg1 Nc7 $14) 18. exf5 $16 gxf5 19. Nd5 Bf6 (19... Rf7
20. g3 Nf6 21. Nb5 $16) 20. Bh6 Ng7 21. Qe2 (21. Qd2 Rf7 $16) 21... e6 (21...
e5 $5 {is noteworthy} 22. Nb5 e4 $14) 22. Nxf6+ $16 Rxf6 23. Qe3 (23. Bd2 $5
$16) 23... e5 $14 24. Bxg7 (24. Bd5+ Nge6 25. Qg3+ Rg6 26. Nxf5 Rxg3 27. Ne7+
Kh8 28. Nxc8 Rg6 29. Nxd6 Rxh6 30. Nf7+ Kg7 31. Nxh6 Kxh6 $16) 24... Kxg7 (
24... exd4 25. Rxd4 Kxg7 26. Qe7+ Rf7 27. Qxd6 $15) 25. Qg5+ Rg6 {Black
threatens to win material: Rg6xg5} 26. Qe7+ Kh6 (26... Kh8 27. Ne2 Re6 28. Qg5
$11) 27. Nb5 {[%cal Rb5d6,Rd1d6,Re7d6,Gg6d6] Increases the pressure on the
backward pawn. White threatens to win material: Nb5xd6} Bxb5 28. Rxd6 {Black
wins a piece.} Be8 $4 (28... Qe8 29. Qh4+ Kg7 30. Rxg6+ hxg6 31. cxb5 $11) 29.
h4 {White has a mate threat} (29. Qf8+ Kg5 30. h4+ Kf4 31. Rxg6 hxg6 32. Qh6+
g5 33. Qxg5#) 29... Rxd6 $4 (29... Bf7 $142 $1 {had to be tried to avoid defeat
} 30. Qxe5 Qf8 $11) 30. Qg5# (30. Qxd6+ $6 {is a useless try} Bg6 31. h5 Qd8
$11) 1-0

