{[%mdl 8192] C01: French: Exchange Variation} 1. d4 e5 2. e3 d5 3. Nc3 exd4 4.
exd4 Nc6 5. Nf3 Bg4 (5... Bb4 6. h3 (6. a3 Bxc3+ 7. bxc3 Nge7 8. Rb1 O-O 9. Bd3
b6 10. O-O Bf5 11. Bxf5 Nxf5 12. Qd3 Qd7 13. Bf4 Rac8 14. Rfe1 f6 15. c4 dxc4
16. Qxc4+ Kh8 17. c3 Na5 18. Qe6 Qxe6 19. Rxe6 g5 20. Bg3 Nxg3 {Bouvet,L (2155)
-Velten,P (2379) Naujac 2012 0-1 (45)}) 6... Bf5 7. Bd3 Nge7 8. O-O Bxc3 9.
bxc3 O-O 10. Ba3 Re8 11. Re1 Bg6 12. c4 dxc4 13. Bxc4 Nf5 14. Rxe8+ Qxe8 15.
Qd2 Nd6 16. Bb3 a5 17. Bxd6 cxd6 18. Ba4 Qd8 19. Re1 Qc7 20. Qe3 {Kosintseva,T
(2536)-Rajlich,I (2465) Ningbo 2009 1/2-1/2 (50)}) 6. h3 $146 {White threatens
to win material: h3xg4} (6. Be2 Bb4 7. O-O Nge7 8. Ne5 Nxe5 9. Bxg4 Bxc3 10.
bxc3 Nxg4 11. Qxg4 O-O 12. Re1 Ng6 13. g3 Re8 14. Bd2 Qd6 15. h4 Re6 16. h5 Nf8
17. Rxe6 Nxe6 18. Re1 Re8 19. h6 g6 20. Qf3 f5 {Vlasak,L (2260)-Strzemiecki,Z 
(2395) Pardubice 2010 0-1 (43)}) 6... Bh5 7. Be2 Nf6 8. Bf4 (8. O-O Bb4 $14)
8... Bd6 {Black threatens to win material: Bd6xf4} 9. Bg3 (9. Bg5 $5 {has some
apparent merit} Be7 10. O-O $14) 9... O-O {Black castles and improves king
safety} 10. O-O Ne7 (10... Bxg3 11. fxg3 Qd6 12. g4 $15) 11. Ne5 Bxe2 {Black
forks: d1+f1} 12. Qxe2 Re8 13. Qd3 c6 {Covers b5} 14. a3 {Secures b4} a6 {
White has a very active position} 15. Rfe1 Nd7 $2 (15... Ng6 16. Nxg6 Bxg3 17.
Ne5 Bxe5 18. Rxe5 Rxe5 19. dxe5 $11) 16. Qf3 $4 {White has let it slip away} (
16. Nxf7 Kxf7 17. Bxd6 Kg8 $16) 16... f6 $2 (16... Bxe5 17. dxe5 g6 18. Bh4 $11
) 17. Nxd7 (17. Nxc6 $142 {would have given White a clear advantage} bxc6 18.
Bxd6 $16) 17... Qxd7 $14 18. Ne2 (18. Bxd6 Qxd6 19. Re3 Ng6 $14) 18... Ng6 19.
Bxd6 Qxd6 20. Ng3 Nh4 {Black threatens to win material: Nh4xf3} (20... Qd7 21.
Rad1 $11) 21. Qg4 {White threatens to win material: Qg4xh4} Ng6 (21... g5 22.
Re2 $11) 22. h4 $14 Re7 $4 (22... Qc7 $142 $5 $14 {would allow Black to play on
}) 23. h5 (23. Nf5 $142 {seems even better} Rxe1+ 24. Rxe1 $18) 23... Nf8 $4 {
the position was bad, and this mistake simply hastens the end} (23... Rae8 $142
24. Red1 Qf4 $18) 24. Nf5 Rxe1+ 25. Rxe1 (25. Rxe1 Qc7 26. Re7 Qxe7 27. Nxe7+
Kf7 28. Nf5 $18) 1-0

