Secures g5} 13. f3 {Prevents intrusion on g4} (13. f4 Ng6 $16) 13... Qc8 (13...
c5 14. Nf5 $11) 14. Nd5 (14. f4 $5 {should be examined more closely} Ng6 15.
Qd3 $14) 14... Nxd5 $11 15. Bxd5 c6 {Black threatens to win material: c6xd5}
16. Ba2 Qc7 17. Qe2 Bf6 18. Rad1 Rad8 (18... Rfe8 19. c3 $11) 19. f4 Ng6 (19...
Nc4 20. Bxc4 bxc4 21. Rfe1 $11) 20. f5 {White wins space} Ne5 21. Nf3 c5 (21...
